# Error Journal

Records **recurring pitfalls** in this project and how they were fixed, so future agents and workers can avoid them.

## Why This File Exists

LLMs repeat the same class of mistakes across sessions (typical examples: misusing a library API, an implicit fixture convention, a toolchain version trap). Without persistence, every occurrence forces gate.sh to bounce it back for a rewrite — wasting tokens and time. Writing down "known traps" lets workers see them upfront and steer clear.

Workers read this file before starting any task.

## What Goes Here / What Doesn't

**Include**:

- The **root cause** of a gate failure (not the symptom itself, but why it happened)
- The same class of error has occurred 2+ times
- Traps that could recur across different tasks
- Temporary workarounds + TODOs (mark `[WORKAROUND]`)

**Exclude**:

- One-off mistakes (belongs to that task's own retry; already handled by the gate)
- Open questions still being debugged (note in the spec first; move here once confirmed)
- Things a code comment explains well enough

## Format

Each entry in reverse chronological order:

```
## YYYY-MM-DD: <one-line symptom>

- Trigger: <what kind of task/operation hits this>
- Symptom: <the error message or test output you'll see>
- Root cause: <the real reason, not the surface error>
- Fix: <how to handle it next time>
- Status: fixed / [WORKAROUND]
```

## Example

```
## 2026-01-20: pytest fixture order causing db test pollution between tests

- Trigger: new test added with fixtures in wrong order
- Symptom: test passes in isolation, some cases FAIL in full suite (order-dependent)
- Root cause: `db_session` fixture depends on `engine` fixture, but conftest had them reversed
- Fix: all db-related tests must have `pytestmark = pytest.mark.usefixtures("clean_db")` at the top
- Status: fixed
```

```
## 2026-02-03: [WORKAROUND] aiohttp 3.9 on macOS sporadic keep-alive hang

- Trigger: sporadic hang ≥ 30s running integration tests
- Symptom: test has no timeout, eventually CI times out entirely
- Root cause: aiohttp 3.9.x + macOS launchd network stack interaction bug (upstream #8421)
- Fix: explicitly `await session.close()` after each session, with `connector_owner=True`
- Status: [WORKAROUND] — revert once aiohttp 3.10 is released
```

